data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"role": "model","parts": [{"text": " the sky appear blue.\n\n**In summary, blue light is scattered more by the atmosphere than other colors, leading us to perceive a blue sky.**\n\n**Why not violet?**\n\n*   Less violet light emitted by the sun.\n*   Human eyes are more sensitive to blue.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*"}]}}],"usageMetadata": {"trafficType": "ON_DEMAND"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.0-flash","createTime": "2025-07-21T21:47:26.729720Z","responseId": "brV-aPjELKynnvgPn-DDkQs"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"role": "model","parts": [{"text": "   **Sunsets and Sunrises:** When the sun is low on the horizon, sunlight has to travel through more of the atmosphere. This means that most of the blue light is scattered away before it reaches our eyes. This leaves the longer wavelengths like orange and red to dominate, resulting in beautiful sunsets and sunr"}]}}],"usageMetadata": {"trafficType": "ON_DEMAND"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.0-flash","createTime": "2025-07-21T21:47:26.729720Z","responseId": "brV-aPjELKynnvgPn-DDkQs"}

